Davenport.F.J. Raible House: The F.J. Raible House is a historic building located in the West End of Davenport, Iowa, United States. F.J. Raible, who worked for a cigar manufacturer, began living in this house in 1884. While this house follows the Greek Revival style, which was very popular in Davenport, it is noteworthy that the main entrance and the windows are set within a slightly recessed plane.
